Thanks Guillaume.  It appears that "find(int ...)" returns the id not the name.  So, I went ahead and added a method:
std::string getFieldName(int id)
{
switch (id)
{
case 0:
return "liquid";
case 1:
  return "gas";

case 2:
  return "drop";

default:
  mooseError("Invalid id for FieldEnum, id = ", id);

}
Just a bit surprised that there isn't a more generic way to do this in Moose as there seems to be multiple ways to do just about anything.
Joe

find with the id as argument should return an iterator which you should be able to use to call name().
MooseEnumBase::find(int id) const
{
  return std::find_if(
      _items.begin(), _items.end(), [&id](MooseEnumItem const & item) { return item.id() == id; });
}


Another option is to call getNames() on the enum and access it at the right position.
